## Our Open Source Commitment

All versions of poko capsule website remain open source with specific commercial restrictions. Modifications must be kept open source under the same licensing scheme. We're committed to transparency and community contribution.

We hope to eventually transition to a fully open source model as the project finds sustainable income sources. By purchasing a commercial license, you're supporting the ongoing development of eco-focused web development tools.

## Frequently Asked Questions

<details>
  <summary>Can I use poko capsule website for my personal blog that has ads?</summary>
  <p>If your blog generates significant revenue through ads, you would need a Commercial License. However, if ad revenue is minimal and just covers hosting costs, you may qualify for Personal Use. Contact us for clarification on your specific case.</p>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>Do I need to renew my Commercial License?</summary>
  <p>You only need to renew if you want to receive updates after the first year. The perpetual use right for the version you purchased never expires.</p>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>As a Reseller, do I need to purchase a license for each client?</summary>
  <p>Yes, each client needs the appropriate license (Personal or Commercial) based on their use case. The Reseller License grants you implementation rights, but end clients still need their own license.</p>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>Can I modify the source code?</summary>
  <p>Yes, all license types permit modifications. However, modifications must remain open source under the same licensing scheme, and you cannot create competing products.</p>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>What jurisdiction governs these licenses?</summary>
  <p>All licenses are governed by the laws of Brussels, Belgium.</p>
</details>

